    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER - FRONT COVER</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FRONT COVER</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="15">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to front cover removal, remove the following components:</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Refer to the appropriate manual section for detailed removal procedures.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>Vibration damper</para>
                <para>Oil pump assembly</para>
                <para>Water inlet elbow</para>
                <para>Water pump and pulley</para>
                <para>Oil pan</para>
                <para>Oil cooler</para>
                <para>Coolant filter and header</para>
                <para>Fuel injection pump</para>
                <para>Fuel injection lines (high and low pressure)</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the serpentine belt and tensioner as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install breaker bar into belt tensioner and remove tension on belt. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050803">8.3</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove serpentine belt.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Return tensioner back to original position and remove breaker bar.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen mounting bolt and remove tensioner. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050804">8.4</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050803" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2355" filename="../figeg2/eg2355.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.3.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Alternator</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Serpentine Belt</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Fan Drive Pulley</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. Vibration Damper</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. Water Pump Pulley</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. Belt Tensioner</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050804" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2362" filename="../figeg2/eg2362.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.4.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Belt Tensioner</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the alternator as follows: Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050805">8.5</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove the lower alternator mounting bolt and the top rolling pin.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the alternator</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove the alternator mounting bracket bolts. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050806">8.6</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the bracket.</para>
                    <figure id="ef1050805" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2443" filename="../figeg2/eg2443.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.5.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Alternator</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Bracket</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050806" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg1604" filename="../figeg1/eg1604.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.6.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fan drive hub and pulley as follows: Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050807">8.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the bolts and fan pulley.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove fan hub drive capscrews and hub. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050808">8.8</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050807" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3015" filename="../figeg3/eg3015.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.7.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Fan Hub Pulley</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Fan Hub Mounting Bolts (6)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050808" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3009" filename="../figeg3/eg3009.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.8.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Bracket</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Fan Hub Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Engines may be equipped with or without an air compressor or power steering pump.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the air compressor and or power steering pump (if applied) as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two bolts securing power steering pump to air compressor (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050809">8.9</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ). If applicable.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen two (2) coolant hose clamps located at the air compressor and crankcase and
                        remove coolant hoses (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050810">8.10</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050809" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3008" filename="../figeg3/eg3008.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.9.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Air Compressor</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Power Steering Pump</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Mounting Bracket</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050810" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3007" filename="../figeg3/eg3007.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.10.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Coolant Line</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Coolant Line</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Air Compressor</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Top coolant hose is permanently attached to air compressor. It will come out when air
                                compressor is removed from front cover.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen two (2) nuts securing oil lubrication line to air compressor. Remove oil line
                        (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050811">8.11</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two (2) bolts securing air compressor bracket to air compressor. Remove
                        bracket (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050812">8.12</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two (2) bolts securing bracket to crankcase. Remove bracket (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050813">8.13</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two (2) bolts securing air compressor to front cover and remove air
                        compressor.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050811" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3006" filename="../figeg3/eg3006.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.11.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Air Compressor</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Lubrication Oil Line</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Nuts (2)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050812" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3005" filename="../figeg3/eg3005.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.12.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Rear Bracket</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050813" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3001" filename="../figeg3/eg3001.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.13.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Air Compressor</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Air Compressor Bracket</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the three fasteners which secure the injection pump drive gear access
                    cover and gasket to front cover. Remove cover and discard the O-Ring. (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050814">8.14</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fuel injection pump. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Section 11, "FUEL INJECTION PUMP."</emph>
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The fuel injection pump drive gear is free and is removed when the front cover is
                            removed.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>PRIOR TO REMOVING THE INJECTION PUMP, FOLLOW THE INJECTION PUMP TO ENGINE TIMING PROCEDURE
                            TO FACILITATE REASSEMBLY, REFER TO SECTION 11.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the front cover as follows:</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The engine may be rotated to the vertical position (front cover facing up) to allow
                            retention of the hardware in the cover.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove all the front cover mounting bolts which secure the front cover
                        (front half) to the rear half of the front cover and crankcase. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050815">8.15</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lift the front cover (with hardware) from the crankcase and set aside.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove front cover gaskets and O-Rings from front cover and discard. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050816">8.16</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050814" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg1793" filename="../figeg1/eg1793.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.14.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Access Cover</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Front Cover</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050815" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2449" filename="../figeg2/eg2449.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.15.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Front Cover</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050816" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2450" filename="../figeg2/eg2450.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.16.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Front Half Front Cover</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Rear Half Front Cover</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil pressure relief valve from front cover (rear half). Mark valve to identify
                    its proper location when installing. (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050817">8.17</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .)
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Valve may be removed by depressing plunger and trapping a length of copper wire when
                            released. Valve may then be removed by copper wire.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>The oil pressure relief valve should be tagged upon removal to ensure identification. DO
                            NOT mix oil pressure relief valve with oil pressure regulator valve (found in side of
                            crankcase).
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1050817" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2455" filename="../figeg2/eg2455.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.17.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Pressure Relief Valve</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Front Cover Rear Half</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
